Monarch Casino Resort, INC | Freuqently Asked Questions









































Home
Frequently Asked Questions



Frequently Asked Questions


Where is Monarch traded and what is the company's stock symbol?
Monarch Casino & Resort, Inc. ("Monarch") common stock is traded on the Nasdaq Stock Market under the symbol MCRI.
Who is the company's Stock Transfer Agent?
Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc.
                  51 Mercedes Way
                  Edgewood, NY 11717
Who is Monarch's Corporate Counsel?
Greenberg Traurig
                  3773 Howard Hughes Parkway
                  Suite 400 North
                  Las Vegas, Nevada 89169
What is the company's fiscal year?
Our fiscal year ends with the calendar year. Our quarters end on March 31, June 30, September 30, and December 31.
Does Monarch pay a cash dividend?
No, we do not pay a cash dividend.
When does the company report earnings?
We usually report earnings approximately two weeks before each SEC quarterly filing is due.
How can an investor contact the company for financial literature, questions, and other requests?
You can Contact Us throughout the website, by phone at 775.335.4600, or by fax at 775.332.9171.
Who can be contacted regarding complaints about the company's accounting, internal auditing controls and/or auditing matters?
Complaints regarding company accounting, internal auditing controls and/or auditing matters may be submitted to:
Designated Ethics Officer ("DEO") - Debra B. Robinson, Esq.
                  3800 South Virginia Street
                  Reno, Nevada 89502
                  775.335.4600
and/or
Chairman of the Audit Committee - Yvette Landau
                  3800 South Virginia Street
                  Reno, Nevada 89502
                  775.335.4600














