RENO, Nev. (AP) _ Monarch Casino & Resort Inc. (MCRI) on Tuesday reported second-quarter earnings of $7.2 million.
The Reno, Nevada-based company said it had profit of 40 cents per share.
The casino operator posted revenue of $58.2 million in the period.
Monarch Casino shares have risen 17 percent since the beginning of the year. In the final minutes of trading on Tuesday, shares hit $30.26, a rise of 28 percent in the last 12 months.
